name: treatment of used window frame, wood, collection for final disposal | used window frame, wood | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/10404/documentation

This dataset describes the disposal of a wooden window frame with 1 m2 visible area via a municipal incineration plant. Distance to incineration site is assumed to be 50 km.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



Included processes are the disposal of wood, paint, rubber, plastic, steel, aluminium, copper and zinc parts, and the transport to the incineration site. Metal parts are too small to be efficiently collected and recycled.
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/382:Waste treatment and disposal/3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Swiss practice of waste management of window frames.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Waste management includes incineration of wood, paint, rubber, plastic, steel, aluminium, copper and zinc parts, and the transport to the incineration site by average 28t lorry.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: see Geography This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Calculation from window frame material composition
